result.name: Aulis Hong Kong

reviews.text: Came here for lunch and ordered the tasting menu (980hkd). Service from kitchen staff was excellent, but not so much the waiting staff. I personally think the meats in the menu were cooked to perfection. However, dishes were quite simple and lacking layers of flavors. Some element of the dishes was used repetitively... quite dull frankly.

Aulis serves a 19 course tasting menu that incorporates dishes from Roganic and will experiment with new dishes. The concept is using local fresh ingredients and letting them shine. They do use some local produce from HK but a lot of the ingredients are from the UK. This is really an experience for foodies to enjoy. It doesn’t come cheap but if you really like innovative cooking that showcases the ingredients then you will enjoy a meal here. 

Food: 4.5 stars
Service/Environment: 5 stars
Value: 4 stars
Overall: 4.5 stars

My favorite dishes of the evening: 

1) Crab, grilled cabbage chicken skin -  I loved that they picked the crab meat out of the shell for you. The crab is paired with a grilled cabbage and crispy chicken skin.  The balance of textures and flavors was fantastic. 

2) Truffle bread budding - A savory take on the classic bread pudding dessert. The truffle isn’t overpowering and adds nice flavor notes to the creamy bread pudding. This is really delicious couple of bites

3) Beef tartare - The tartare is chopped in small cubes and the texture is similar to at a chopped tuna sashimi. The smoked coal oil gives the taste of light charcoal from a grill.  The balance of flavors is really unique and interesting. 

4) Beetroot with eel - This was a really tasty bite. I enjoyed the crispy ness of the eel paired with the bright and vibrant sweetness of the red beats. Would really be a nice canopy served at a party.
overrated

reviews.text:
Food: good ingredients but some dishes too much sauce. Nice presentation. 

Service: can be much better, we didn't enjoy the service but we felt that all the staff were in a rush, they could not wait for you to finish your meal and take away your plates. The introduction of each dish could be more passionate instead of just a speedy robot talking.

Atmosphere: totally not fine dining standard, especially with this price. It is an open space with a low ceiling, a bit hard to find the entrance of the restaurant if they don't have the temporary hoarding at the corridor area. More like a upgraded food court.
My favourite! Super good food with very affordable and reasonable  price! Good service ! Big range of wine , many selection ! Spacious and good deco! Also have a private room for party !

One of the best restaurants I have ever had the pleasure to dine in. It was my birthday today and we enjoyed the full  tasting menu.
A journey through taste,texture and colours. 
Everyone in the team  had a role to play explaining and presenting the dishes, which they had obviously tasted as they did so with great knowledge, passion. and excitement. This to me is infectious. Would love to try Aulis at some point. A worthy 5 stars ⭐️

Modern British cuisine, the taste of fresh produce is certainly appreciated. Beautiful food presentation like in a fine dining restaurant. Definitely Great value for lunch, just a slightly odd location to be in Sino Plaza. Overall amazing experience with friendly service.

Bread butter was how you’d assume. Bread & butter but so good we ordered twice! As fine dining goes in HK, this is value for money and the waiter was weird yet entertaining. Watch him karate chop the candle lights!
